<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-12T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-12T03:00:00-05:00" n="1133" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1133">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/10–1249: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                            the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-12T16:00:00+08:00">October 12,
                                1949—4 p. m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received October 12—5:23 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>4294. ReConGentel 4219, October 8. Isbrandtsen SS <hi rend="italic">Flying
                            Trader</hi> etd<note n="83" xml:id="d1133fn83">Estimated time of
                            departure.</note> from Shanghai October 15. Department will recall this
                        ship eluded Nationalist warships, entering port while warships absent
                        escorting <hi rend="italic">Flying Independent</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Clipper</hi> to Chusan area. Department may wish call attention
                        Nationalist Government imminent departure this vessel in order that incident
                        may be avoided.</p>
                    <p>Sent Department; repeated Embassy Canton 1155, Hong Kong 309.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">McConaughy</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>